{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/pulls/1110","id":683231645,"node_id":"MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NjgzMjMxNjQ1","html_url":"https://github.com/sktime/sktime/pull/1110","diff_url":"https://github.com/sktime/sktime/pull/1110.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/sktime/sktime/pull/1110.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/1110","number":1110,"state":"closed","locked":false,"title":"Governance changes: clearer timelines and conditions for decision making","user":{"login":"fkiraly","id":7985502,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc5ODU1MDI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7985502?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly","html_url":"https://github.com/fkiraly","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/fkiraly/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"body":"Update with final state - based on iterations, some of the timelines and case distinctions have been removed. New diff:\r\n\r\nMajor changes:\r\n* making concrete conditions for core developers becoming active or inactive\r\n* making explicit that core developer approval for proposals must be by a core developer who is not the proposer\r\n* clarified where approvals/rejections must be put (GitHub), spelling out conditions for accept/reject\r\n* removed the gummi condition on \"major change\" (no definition, no decision maker who declares someting a \"major change\")\r\n* added 10 days as a reasonable waiting period, then PR goes to tech meeting and gets a reviewer assigned\r\n* clarified when STEPs are needed, and that it must contain a design (not just a wishlist)\r\n* formulation about encouraging contributors \"from groups underrepresented in the tech sector\" added\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nFor consideration in the 2021-07-05 CC meeting, I've drafted proposed changes to the governance guidelines that aim to make decision conditions for PR acceptance clearer and put clear timelines on decisions.\r\n\r\nMajor changes:\r\n* making concrete conditions for core developers becoming active or inactive\r\n* making explicit that core developer approval for proposals must be by a core developer who is not the proposer\r\n* added lazy lazy approval for proposals made by core devs (new), so core dev PRs do not indefinitely lie around without approval - this is based on assumption that core devs know what they are doing\r\n* clarified where approvals/rejections must be put\r\n* replaced the gummi condition on \"major change\" (no definition, no decision maker who declares someting a \"major change\") with a clear rule on when sth is considered a \"major change\" - based on explicit core dev statement\r\n* added timelines for core dev consideration and decision making - 3 work days for non-major change, 12 work days for major change, 25 work days for stage 3 vote (if needed)\r\n* clarifying what happens if lazy consensus is found (was not stated) - then PR must be merged by a core dev\r\n* clarified that STEP must contain at least high-level design\r\n\r\nThere's one other unrelated change to the sentence at the start, about welcoming people \"who have experienced discrimination\" in the past. I'm not sure it's a good idea do define groups by their suffering rather than self-stated labels or qualifiers, so I changed it to \"groups underrepresented in the tech sector\".","created_at":"2021-07-04T20:22:12Z","updated_at":"2021-10-23T10:16:45Z","closed_at":"2021-10-